tasks all`\n*   **Inspect Tasks:** Use the `show` command to view task metadata and the `task.md` description.\n    *   **Command:** `mycli task-hall show <task-id>`\n*   **State Directory:** `D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\task-hall\\state\\`\n    *   `listings.json`: Index of all tasks.\n    *   `tasks/<task_id>/task.md`: Detailed task instructions, constraints, and **Claim Thresholds** (Complexity & Model Tier).\n\n### 2. Heartbeat & Lifecycle: `agent-cli mount`\nThe \"heartbeat\" mechanism is implemented via `mycli agent-cli mount`. It keeps an agent session alive by periodically \"ticking\" and sending a lifecycle prompt.\n\n*   **Mechanism:** Uses Windows Task Scheduler to run a heartbeat every $N$ minutes.\n*   **Heartbeat Prompt:** Instructs the agent to inspect context, continue work, or schedule its own next wake-up.\n*   **End Marker:** If the agent outputs `AGENT_CLI_LIFECYCLE_END`, the lifecycle terminates or cycles to a new session.\n*   **Commands:**\n    *   **List Mounts:** `mycli agent-cli mount list`\n    *   **Show Status:** `mycli agent-cli mount show <mount-id>`\n    *   **Manual Tick:** `mycli agent-cli mount tick <mount-id>`\n*   **State Path:** `D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\agent-cli\\state\\mounts\\`\n\n### 3. Scheduling: `mycli agent-cli schedule add`\nThis command schedules a **one-time** future agent session wake-up using Windows Task Scheduler. It is often used by agents themselves to \"pause and resume\" or by operators to defer tasks.\n\n*   **Expected Usage:**\n    ```powershell\n    # Relative delay (e.g., 30m, 2h, 1d)\n    mycli agent-cli schedule add --in 30m --agent opencode/private-assistant --prompt \"Resume checking the build logs\"\n    \n    # Absolute time\n    mycli agent-cli schedule add --at \"2026-04-25 18:30\" --agent opencode/private-assistant --prompt \"Daily report generation\"\n    ```\n*   **Key Logic (File: `agent-cli.ps1`):**\n    *   Creates a scheduled task in the `\\agent-cli\\` task path.\n    *   Persists a record in `D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\agent-cli\\state\\schedules\\`.\n    *   Supports session continuity via `--continue` or `--session <id>`.\n*   **Inspection:** `mycli agent-cli schedule list`\n\n### Summary Table\n\n| Operational Area | Action | Primary Command / Path |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **Task Discovery** | List available work | `mycli task-hall tasks listed` |\n| **Task Detail** | Read task instructions | `mycli task-hall show <task-id>` |\n| **Heartbeat** | Monitor active lifecycles | `mycli agent-cli mount list` |\n| **Scheduling** | Add future wake-up | `mycli agent-cli schedule add --in <delay> --prompt <text>` |\n| **State Storage** | Global task index | `capability-library/mycli/task-hall/state/listings.json` |\n\n<task_metadata>\nsession_id: ses_23e23b93cffe4juG3UwpTY2oqA\n</task_metadata>\n\nto continue: task(session_id=\"ses_23e23b93cffe4juG3UwpTY2oqA\", load_skills=[], run_in_background=false, prompt=\"...\")","metadata":{"truncated":false,"prompt":"Explore this workspace for heartbeat/task-hall operational context. Find where current worker should check for active work, how to inspect listed tasks, and how scheduling via `mycli agent-cli schedule add` is expected to be used. Focus on capability-library/mycli and any relevant docs. Return concise findings with file paths/commands.","agent":"Sisyphus-Junior","category":"quick","load_skills":[],"description":"Inspect heartbeat docs","run_in_background":false,"sessionId":"ses_23e23b93cffe4juG3UwpTY2oqA","command":"heartbeat-analyze","model":{"providerID":"MoreCode","modelID":"gemini-3-flash"}},"title":"Inspect heartbeat docs","time":{"start":1777073931930,"end":1777073981610}},"id":"prt_dc1dc466c001N9g1kQN1D7x2Hi","sessionID":"ses_23e2400e1ffeWwNCRgm2Y5dDGh","messageID":"msg_dc1dbffa5001hHoMpeq6g6uQV4"}}
